H0.text: Who was Poet Laureate from 1850 to 1892. Robert Browning

H1.text: Who was Poet Laureate from 1850 to 1892. Elizabeth Barrett Browning

H2.text: Who was Poet Laureate from 1850 to 1892. Matthew Arnold

H3.text: Who was Poet Laureate from 1850 to 1892. Tennyson

A4.text: In 1850, after Wordsworth's death and Samuel Rogers' refusal, Tennyson was appointed Poet Laureate; Elizabeth Barrett Browning and Leigh Hunt had also been considered. He held the position until his death in 1892, the longest tenure of any laureate.

A5.text: He was Poet Laureate of the United Kingdom during much of Queen Victoria's reign.
